[SN]TITLE[SN]
Claudio Ranieri: Leicester 'will continue to dream' of title

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Leicester City manager Claudio Ranieri says he does not want to be woken up from his Premier League title dream.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Foxes are five points clear of Tottenham at the top of the table, following Saturday's 3-1 win over Manchester City at Etihad Stadium.
Ranieri, 64, insists his players are not feeling the tension even though his team are now the bookmakers' favourites to win the Premier League title.
"It's a great story so why the pressure? Let's enjoy," he said.
"I hope the bookmakers, this time, are right but I am very pragmatic.
